PaperPlayer is an open-source android music application which provides a user with simplicity as well as productivity. It comes with a clean materialistic design.

Its a simple Android music player meant to be the base platform for some ideas that are centered around making listening to music a more enjoyable activity.

It was built by MichealObi and its provided at no cost.

Alongside being able to play and listen to music, there is the option for the creation of playlists.


Features

*Its a simple Music player

*Ability to add, delete and sort music into playlists

*Material design

*Can sort music into albums,artists and genre

*Focused on design

*Open-source

*More features coming soon


With the light, intuitive and easy to use features of PaperPlayer, it is the music player you can use on the Go.
